context: The <a0_0><a1_0>National Archives<a0_0/> and Records Administration<a1_0/> (NARA) is an <b3_0>independent<b3_0/> agency of the United States government charged with preserving and documenting <b2_0>government and historical records<b2_0/> and with increasing public access to those documents, which comprise the National Archives. NARA is officially responsible for maintaining and publishing the legally authentic and authoritative copies of <b4_0>acts of Congress, presidential proclamations and executive orders, and federal regulations<b4_0/>. The NARA also transmits <b5_0>votes<b5_0/> of the <b6_0>Electoral College<b6_0/> to Congress.
